# Project: Africa Risk Map

## What this is

A multi-tenant B2B platform for Human Risks / Lombard Insurance (the Insurer) and its brokers to manage Personal Accident (PA) risk across Africa for member-based client organisations — starting with GRAA (Game Rangers Association of Africa). It combines a sub-nationally-rated territory risk map, organisation/location/headcount tracking, an AI-assisted policy-structuring workflow, and a premium & aggregate calculator that reconciles exactly with each client's issued Policy Schedule.

Not a generic demo — this replaces a set of Excel workbooks (risk rating table + monthly premium/agg ledger) with a governed, auditable system of record. Scaffolded from the [cursor-guardrails](https://github.com/AGM82/cursor-guardrails) template so the 7-tier guardrail system is present from the first commit.

The full product/architecture plan lives at `.cursor/plans/africa-risk-map-platform-plan.md` — treat it as the detailed source of truth behind this summary; consult it for anything not covered here.

## Domain glossary

- **Territory** — A country or rated sub-region (e.g. "Nigeria North-East" vs "Nigeria - Rest of", "DRC East" vs "DRC West"). Carries 6 risk sub-scores (Healthcare Infrastructure, Medical Personnel, Medical Transport, Emergency Response, Security/Conflict, Occupational Hazards), a computed Total Score, Risk Category (Low/Medium/High/Very High/Extreme), evacuation paths/cost, an Evacuation Feasibility flag, and versioned history. Shared, global — one source of truth across all clients.
- **Client** — An insured association/organisation (e.g. GRAA). Owns its own Policy, MemberOrganisations, and RiskMixPolicy.
- **BrokerOrganisation** / **ClientBrokerAssignment** — The brokerage servicing a Client, effective-dated so a broker change at renewal doesn't lose history.
- **MemberOrganisation** — An organisation belonging to a Client (e.g. a specific reserve/park operator).
- **OrganisationLocation** — A MemberOrganisation's presence in a Territory, with a headcount and an assigned CoverCategory.
- **Policy** — One per Client per annual term (GRAA renews 1 December). Has `policyYear`, inception/expiry, status, and links to CoverCategory/PaymentTerms. Historical terms load as prior Policy records for audit.
- **CoverCategory** — The Insured-Person Categories within a Policy (e.g. "Category 1 — Essential", "Category 2 — Premium"). Carries a policy-year-specific display label mapped onto an underlying PlanType (Essential/Premium), declared insured-person count, and Premium/Aggregate rate lines (amount + basis + VAT treatment).
- **BenefitLine** — A benefit (DEATH/PTD/TTD/MEDICAL/EVACUATION) within a CoverCategory, with its sum insured/limit and basis.
- **PaymentTerms** — How a Policy bills (e.g. `MONTHLY_BY_NUMBERS`, `ANNUAL_WITH_ADJUSTMENT`) and whether the Aggregate is a fund the client retains.
- **TerritoryBenefitEligibility** — Maps a Territory's Benefit Options Available (1-2 / 3-4 / 4 only / Decline) to which CoverCategory values a location there may use — the underwriting-gate data.
- **Endorsement** — A headcount add/remove against an OrganisationLocation; the ledger, replacing the Excel rows.
- **RecalibrationBatch** — Tracks the one-time reconciliation of newly-entered organisations/locations against known ledger totals until balanced.
- **RiskMixPolicy** — Per-client target % of covered lives across risk tiers (e.g. ~85% Low/Med, 10% High, 5% Very High), with a tolerance band protecting the client's rate guarantee.
- **PolicyTemplate** — A reusable, not-yet-client-bound CoverCategory/BenefitLine/PaymentTerms shape, used to seed a new client.
- **PolicyStructureSession** — The audit trail behind the AI-assisted "Structure Chat" policy-drafting feature.
- **ExternalSignal** — An AI/feed-sourced candidate risk-relevant event (conflict, outbreak, disaster, advisory change) with mandatory source/quote/snapshot provenance; advisory only, Insurer-gated, never auto-repricing.

